/// The Pkl package that carries THIS home's live data — today just the
/// generated `dump.pkl` (the typed entity/area/floor dump `PklDump` renders
/// from the live HA registry). Entries depend on it under the alias
/// `@fh-home`, so an entry writes `import "@fh-home/dump.pkl" as dump`.
///
/// Why this is its own package, separate from `@fh-dashboard` (ADR 0010):
/// the two artifacts have opposite lifecycles. The library in `lib/` is shared,
/// versionable, and one day publishable to a registry; the dump is per-home,
/// regenerated from the live instance, and can NEVER ship in a published
/// package — decoupling it from the live home is exactly the thing the whole
/// endpoint exists to avoid. Keeping it here means publishing `@fh-dashboard`
/// only flips the consumer's mapping; the dump stays local either way, and
/// entries never change.
///
/// `dump.pkl` reaches the domain schema through the `@fh-dashboard` dependency
/// below (`import "@fh-dashboard/hass.pkl"`) rather than as a file sibling, so
/// its `hass` types are the SAME module identity `components.pkl` sees. That is
/// load-bearing — see ADR 0010, "Module identity".
amends "pkl:Project"

package {
  name = "fh-home"
  baseUri = "package://fh.invalid/fh-home"
  version = "1.0.0"
  packageZipUrl = "https://fh.invalid/fh-home@\(version).zip"
}

dependencies {
  ["fh-dashboard"] = import("../lib/PklProject")
}
